I started to worry they might of harmed themselves. Thankfully after a couple months I finally got messages back from them. They reassured me everything was okay. 

While moving from the GTA to Kingston they had ended up losing their phone. A family issue led her to moving back home and she had gotten a phone from her sister. Hearing from her and her letting me know everything was okay definitely erased the stress I had been feeling.
Specific Event: Recieving texts back from my friend

Recall: When I got recognition for passing a module very well last year after not doing very well in the past.
I felt excitement when I discovered a Reiki course that I wanted to study. I felt particularly draw to study this healing method and found a local opportunity to study this.
Specific Event: Because I feel a closeness to this area of study

Recall: I saw a post on Facebook, It was a video of a guy in tears and praying for children he saw selling on the road so they could have money for food he bought everything from the kids so they could go home ,the video was captioned with his story of how he was once in the same situation and how he is now successful. I admired him for how hard he worked to get where he is today.
I had some tests done at the hospital and when I get the results everything was ok.  I felt shear relief

I went for a job interview and felt which went very well, there was a lot of things that felt right. and of which the interviewer seemed very happy with I felt Optimistic of the out come of the interview

Me and my previous line manager had a difference with my KPI. I told my manager that they were being unfair to rate me on the work they never even tasked me with. I had to tell the manager I do not approve of their leadership style and will seek intervention from HR.
Specific Event: Being unfairly rated for performance review.

Recall: I had an issue with someone once and said something that u felt disgust with myself at.  The argument was not a good one and i did feel bad after with myself,
When my household had to isolate because one person had Covid, I offered to organise buying groceries for the person who had Covid to make sure they were ok and had all they needed.
Specific Event: I went out of my way to do something that this per

Recall: I had been waiting in for a delivery for days, they didn't say when it would arrive. Then one morning I needed to go out to the shops, and when I got back I discovered that the postman had rung the doorbell and got no answer, so I missed the parcel.

I was just walking on the road and then I heard someone scream behind me. I turned around and I saw two boys running away from a woman. They seem to be related to the woman but I felt remorse for not going up to the woman and asking her if she is alright.

I felt a strong desire for someone that I couldn't have, or even be friends with. It was very difficult because I saw that person everyday, I think they felt the same way but nothing ever happened between us.
A motorist cut me off on a roundabout without accepting how dangerous and inconsiderate what they were doing was

I live in a corner house and every single day when I return home from work, someone is blocking my drive with their car. Delivery drivers, other neighbours, relatives of the neighbours. So I have to park down the street and walk back to my home.
Specific Event: Being blocked out of my own drive again

Recall: I remember when I received my A level results when I was 18. I had always been a conscientious and high-achieving student throughout my entire school career. There had been no advance warning, my mock results had been fine. So when I opened my results I was very unpleasantly surprised to find my results were bad. It was so disappointing that I think it affected me for a long time. I didn't even think of sitting retakes. It affected my future plans.
Specific Event: Doing worse in my A level results than expected.

Recall: One of my friends was having a hard time mentally, and needed someone to talk to. i took the time to listen to their problems, not interjecting at any points, and was able to be there with them in their hard times. Talking wasn't needed while there, the only thing i had to do was sit with them and listen to what they had to say, and allow them to know that someone was there for them.

I realised I loved spending time with this person and hated leaving them - I would think about them all the time we were apart. This person made me feel happy, supported, and made me laugh all the time
Specific Event: Being helped through a difficult family time

Recall: I went out with a friend who was having a hard time and she was enjoying herself, watching the smile on her face made me feel joy.

My boyfriend had just got in from work, my brother and his wife were here, he called me out of the room to have a word with him, when I left the room, he said he thought he might be having a heart attack, he then collapsed, the ambulance was called, followed by the air ambulance, the emergency services were really struggling to keep him alive, he did at hospital shortly after.
Specific Event: The death of a partner and dear friend.

Recall:
In the middle of the night, I heard a noise coming from the garden. It was an unusual noise, one I have not heard before.
I got out of bed, went downstairs and turned the lights on, only to realise there was fox climbing up and down the fence.

A few years ago I came down to my rowing club to go out in my boat, only to discover that someone had taken my blades and was using them in another boat. I was very angry that they had taken my private blades instead of the ones belonging to the club that are for everyone's use. I had to use other blades which were not my own and were not set up for me. I was also angry because then the other person using my blades was coming in to land they scraped my blades on the concrete step, not taking the same care with them as I would have done.
Specific Event: The fact that someone had taken my property

Recall: One of the key project was taken from me and given to someone last year so I felt that I dont have skill set and ability to work on that type of projects. I kept thinking why it happened and why I was unsuccessful.
Specific Event: Key project at work was taken from me.

Recall: This happened to me just this week, just over two years ago my husband had an operation to remove a bowel cancer since then all scans and tests have showed no return of the cancer. However periodically since his chemotherapy ended he has become quite ill for weeks at a time. He is convinced he is very close to the end of his life. About 6 weeks after the op my husband was started on a course of chemotherapy which made him very ill and he was hospitalised for several weeks. After recently becoming very ill and eventually collapsing I began to wonder if the chemotherapy had caused long term problems. My curiosity led me to do a lot of research and found that this was indeed a possibility, I also spoke to his cancer nurse who agreed with me an suggested he consult his GP who could provide medication to combat or even reverse these effects. My husband is a very stubborn man and say as he is improving he can't see the point in bothering the doctor. The upcome is we are still fighting about this.
Specific Event: I was worried about my husband's health

Recall: When I was seven I wanted to be a doctor, it wasn't just a fleeting idea but an intense feeling that I had to be a doctor. I was so curious as to how the body worked and wanted to learn more about it, because of this I got a huge anatomical encyclopaedia and every night I would spend hours highlighting and learning all the contents of the book.
I felt sadness when I went to the hospital to visit my sick Mother and saw that she was deteriorating.

The day my dog died was one of the very worst days of my life. I cannot put into word the absolute devastation and loneliness of burying him and knowing we were no longer going to spend all of our time together. I knew my entire world was different and was going to have less joy. My dog got run over in front of me. The was no vet open and it took him 25 minutes to die in a car on the way to another vet really far away. I was inconsolable and 5 years later cannot even think of my dog without tearing up. He was my best friend.
Specific Event: death of my pet due to being run over by a car

Recall: Recently when studying for a test, I was doing a lot of practice tests. However, There was one type of problem which I had a big problem with. I just couldn't figure out how to do those types of problems. Finally, after studying for a while, I looked at the lecture notes and realized that I could simply do it a different way, which helped me solve those types of problems. I had realization when I realized this
When my cat who I thought was gone - as she had been missing for over a week which was extremely unusual for her - returned home.
I felt gratitude when I got confirmation from my colleagues that I was a pleasure to work with. without me having to pry for that confirmation myself.
Specific Event: felling appreciated by people who know me

Recall: I watched my friend put a dog treat in his mouth and let his dog eat it out of his mouth and lick all over his lips and face after getting the treat, my friend then didnt even wipe his face and licked his lips after.

Being able to see a friend I hadn't been able to see in a long while. I was able to book a flight to go and see them in Germany for the first time in years. I spent the night sleepless and excited. The trip to the airport felt exciting and I was happy to be there and to get on the plane. Being able to see them at the airport when I landed felt like a big relief and I was so happy I was in tears. It just felt so good to be with someone after so long.
Specific Event: Seeing someone I hadn't been able to see in a whil

Recall: Whilst working at my desk in a busy office, I needed to take a moment to stretch and I extended my arms really high into the air to have a really good stretch.  A colleague sitting a few feet away pointed out really loudly that I had a hole in my jumper, under my armpit and he exclaimed how surprised he was at that and proceeded to tell my other nearby colleagues.  He went on about my holy jumper for a good hour after spotting the offence, and also told colleagues who were not there at the time, but came into the office later. I felt awkward as I am usually very smart in the office and take a lot of pride in my appearance.  I did feel ashamed that I had let my standards slip and even worse as someone else had spotted it.
Specific Event: My colleague spotting a hole that I was unaware of

Recall: I had parked my car in a city that I did not know well and went into the city centre to shop. I had a lovely time and when I decided to go home I had total forgotten where my car was and I had lost my bearings. It took me a long time to find my car and I think it was just luck but when I did I was so relieved and happy.
Specific Event: Finding my car so I could go home.

Recall:
I have been going to the same gym on and of for a number of years now and there is a woman there who when starting off was very petit and and slim and seemed as though she wanted to gain weight.

after all the years seeing her progress i have gained admiration for her as not only does she seem to have hit her goal, she done so in a manner which was was impressive.
Specific Event: seeing a friend reach their goal

Recall: I felt disapproval after a colleague did something i thought was not right at all. It was related to a patient at work
My husband took my little boy shopping for the groceries-he came home with some flowers and chocolates for me too
Specific Event: It was unexpeted and cheered me up

Recall: When I first started my degree in London, the City was very new to me because I was used to rural countryside. I remember trying to figure out for the first time by myself how to attempt to use the Underground (Tube). The London underground map looked overwhelming and made me feel lost and confused before I had even started my journey from Point A to Point B. In the end I just got on what I hoped was the right tube line because it was stressing me out trying to figure it out and I figured I could always ask someone if I got totally lost.
Specific Event: Different system of travel in new city

Recall: Just today, a good friend that I massively admire, said I was really good with money. He has high standards for himself, and I felt included somehow in his 'being good at useful things' club!
Specific Event: Recognition of being good at something!

Recall: Was in the school library, and received the e-mail from my preferred university saying I was offered a place; the odds were pretty low and I didn't expect it, so I was pretty happy.

I am a musician. I've played guitar for more years than I care to remember, but, I'll never forget the first time I played in front of a large audience. I was a member of a band called Lightning Lloyd and the Flaming Flamingos and we were hired to play at a rally for teachers in Montreal. We had played in small bars and dance halls before, but that day we would play in front of 15,000 people. I  was so nervous I was shaking. I was so afraid that I would make a mistake, but, I sucked it up and took a deep breath, and went on with the show. All went well and we were a hit.
Specific Event: Playing in front of a very large audience.

Recall: I had planned an get together for my birthday with my friends. They all agreed to come and we made plans together. Everyone pulled out last minute and I was extremely disappointed.

I was outside my house about to get into my car and five guys walked up behind me and one of them put his arm around me from the back and showed me a gun and said give me your keys. I gave them the keys but then my tried to push me through the passenger door onto the back seat. I was terrified to go with them as I knew it would not end well. However, at the same time I knew they might shoot me if I resisted. However, the fear of going with them won out and I resisted like crazy and screamed repeatedly. They eventually gave up and roared off with the car.
Specific Event: The gun plus the thought of going with them.

Recall: I saw an old lady who had fallen over on the path in the winter,she was struggling to get up,so i went over and helped her to her feet
i started a walking and water challenge at the start of the year and when i do well and get support from the group it helps inspire those feelings
Specific Event: getting fit and meeting new people

Recall: The last time I felt really surprised was when my parents bought me a car. I really needed a new car, and had been looking on the market for one, but my parents had seemed to hold something back when I was shopping around with them. They bought me a car! Which was awesome! It's a Volvo S60, which I love!
Specific Event: My parents buying me a car

Recall:
A couple of weeks ago, I had an emotional breakdown episode in which I had a strong feeling of wanting to be around people. I spent the holidays entirely alone. And I was mostly trying to suppress or ignore these feelings by keeping myself busy until I couldn't anymore.
The breakdown had occurred during and after I finished watching a Netflix series. I believe my mind just projected the feeling of loneliness into one of the characters.
Specific Event: Relating to the tv show character

Recall: I recently have just received a promotion at work and as a result have been assigned a new project. I felt very nervous that I (actually) don't know anything and that I will underperform in this project. I'm also taking over another member of staff, and when she was in that post she was very capable.
Specific Event: Worry of not being able to perform at work

Recall: I went outside the other day for a walk and didn't know the exact temperature of the air. I knew it was cold so I dressed accordingly but I didn't know how cold it really was. Turns out it was super cold, cold enough that it took me by surprise because I didn't expect it to be that cold.

I was working with my dad and damaged a bath that we were meant to keep when working for a customer who was a bit funny. I was expecting it to turn into a horrible situation as it was a job that we had only just started and we needed the money, so I became anxious and nervous about the outcome.
Specific Event: The potential reactions of other people.

Recall: I had to do a presentation of my schoolwork but I was not fully prepared. Furthermore, I had misinterpreted the starting time, due to different time zones. As a result, I had to present a half-done article.
I tried to get my friend to look at a picture that I had forgotten I doctored and it was shown to them.
Specific Event: Showing my friend an image that was doctored.

Recall: Well after missing my period, I took a pregnancy test only to find it was positive - I was utterly shocked and surprised honestly.
When i did well at something at work then felt optimistic about my abilities, i did a task that i didn't think i was would do well in

There was once a time when in our first year one of our roommates decided to use our shared toiled and then not flush afterwards and when I walked in, I was in for a big surprise that cause to lose my appetite for the whole day

I was getting a lift home from my brother and went home via a back/country road. We pulled out of a junction and a van approaching at high speed almost collided with the passenger side door and hit me.

Recall:
when my daughter came out of an oxygen tent
my daughter was born premature and we spent a few worried months worried whether she would live or die

Recall: I attended a musical concert given by my daughters school , she was one of the performers and was due to play a pieice on the classical guitar that I had been teaching her for some time. The piece was causing her some difficulties and at times had led to some conflict between us. She played it very well and I felt very proud of her for playing in such as wonderful way and overcoming the difficulties.

Recall: A few years ago my neighbors dog was looking very sick. The dog was throwing up. I took one look at the dog and told them that the dog has been poisoned and they rushed him to the vet..
I was carrying a tray of drinks to a group of people sat at a table.  As I was handing a person their drink, the tray tipped forward and the rest of the drinks fell over, spilling their contents

i was sad when i found out that my mom died. she had breast cancer. i was 15 years old and my uncle told me about it. there's not much more to explain. i was at home, he was at the hospital at the time
This was when I was accepted to study at university. I felt pride because in that moment I realized that all the hard work I'd put in to studying in high school paid off
watching my football team score a goal to win the game in the last minute, meaning that they progress into the final
Specific Event: the feeling of relief and joy combined

Recall: On New Years Eve, my husband gave me some money to got up to the bar and order some drinks. On returning to the table holding I went to place a double gin and tonic on the table and the glass hit the table and shattered, sending gin, tonic, glass and loads of ice everywhere.  I helped to clear it all up with the bar staff.
Specific Event: Everbody stopped talking and looked at me.

Recall: Completing my Law degree I felt proud that my studies were completed satisfactorily I was glad that I was able to graduate and move on to the next stage of my career.
Specific Event: The relief and satisfaction of my family

Recall: the time i fell in love when i held my child in my arms for the first time i can still remember the feelings no words can describe . she was so small and innocent and her tender little hand held on to my finger when placed into her hand. this to me was love at first sight for my child

I was woken by people shouting outside my home at 3 in the morning. Turned out to be friends who had no where to sleep and wanted to be let in and crash on the sofa, no big deal. But I was grouchy and told them to go away. Still feel remorse for being unhelpful.

I had the urge to start learning about shares and the stock market. I began my journey by reading articles and playing on a virtual system. 
I then took the plunge with my own money.
Specific Event: The complexity of learning a volatile system

Recall: In a group project, there was one person who had failed to do their part. The group was worried as that missing work was crucial for the project. We all then decided to spend a lot of time at the last minute to complete that part as well. I felt a lot of gratitude to my remaining group members and they as well to me.

The most recent time I have felt fear was when camping on a hilltop in Cornwall during a 100-mile hike. I was in my tent, alone; it was extremely windy. My friends were nearby, in their own tents, but the wind was so loud that they couldn't hear me. The gale was such that the tent poles were bending in on me, concave, and I thought it was going to fall down. I began getting dressed with a view to possibly having to evacuate if the tent blew down. I texted my friends; it didn't deliver (no signal? internet turned off?). Then, horrifyingly, I heard the zip of the front flap of the tent come down: was someone coming into the tent? I also heard what sounded like flip-flops padding around the tent, and dreaded an intruder.

When a friend with mental illnesses texted me to ask how to get somewhere.  It was only a local trip and I was about to do something at home, but I know she doesn't deal well with directions. So I spend some time trying to work out where she was going and when; in the end had to ring her up as it was too complicated to do via texts.
Specific Event: I knew she'd struggle with this and I could help.

Recall: My father in-law contracted cancer.  I realsied that I hadn't seen him for many years, and due to COVID would be unlikely to see him again

A time when I felt curious to do something would be say when I'm playing a computer game and I was playing games like dark souls and there's always a different style of play etc and it makes me curious to see how to progress with different tactics etc
Specific Event: Being able to change weapons etc in game

Recall: I thought that the world-famous Welsh football player Aaron Ramsey had been signed by Cheltenham FC. So I told my son this story which he laughed at. Then followed the usual Internet search and finally after a long discussion we found it WAS Aaron Ramsey, just not THAT Aaron Ramsey, a young kid going on loan to a lowly football club to get some experience. The surprise was that I had remembered everything correctly - names, the loan, the club.

My wife and I are cold water swimmers. There are occasions however when I don't want to do it, feel put off etc my wife however is very driven and motivated. Last weekend we swam in the sea and I held back to capture my wife's experience. She did not hesitate and appeared to embrace every moment she was in the sea, I felt admiration then.
Specific Event: My wife's determination, commitment and courage.

Recall:
There is a large tree outside my kitchen / lounge window, and often there are some pigeons who like to sit on the branches. I always keep an eye out for them because they are nice to look at, and are very large and round. 
When I see them, I try to get their attention and make eye contact with them. When this happens they often will look at me, turning their heads in a quizzical fashion, bobbing up and down, and generally just staring at me as I wave at them.
Specific Event: The quizzical looks from the pigeons

Recall: seeing my granddaughter opening her Christmas presents, she she spend a long tome opening a particular box then put it back under the tree so she could find it again
Specific Event: wanting to re- find the present

Recall: I was asked out on a date by a colleague he was charming funny and seemed really interested i hadnt been working there very long and he worked in an upstairs department i agreed to go on a date with him but asked my other colleague to come along with me  for support i couldnt believe what happened
Specific Event: he was married to my chaparone

Recall: It all happened when i was in my freshman year of college,back in 2015. I needed to attend a late event on campus and it was not something i would usually do. Everything was going on so well at the event that i almost didn't think id have to go home after that.Well time came that i need to go home, i had to wait for my parents to come fetch me. i didn't inform them in time so that meant having to wait outside for a little bit longer. I got very worried when it was getting late and by each minute my fear became more.
When I spoke to my brother when had had relationship troubles, I comforted and cared for him when he was upset.
I had been for a night out to a restaurant.  I arrived home and realised I had left my phone on the restaurant table.
I felt deep grief a few years ago when my father died. He was in reasonable health but died in his sleep unexpectedly.

A few years ago I was trying to find a job, I needed money to pay rent for a student house I was in. I applied for a factory job and a few days later I received an email saying that I was to come in for an interview. The interview was scheduled a few days after I got the email, every time I thought about it I got nervous and had this feeling in the pit of my stomach which I always get when I'm nervous. The day of the interview came along with the same feelings but they went away during the interview and a few days later I received a call saying I got the job.
I felt like we had always been together, I could see no faults and used no reasons but lived in the love I felt.
Specific Event: An event did not cause me to feel love.

Recall: I experienced grief when my mother passed away. It was so sudden and she died at an early age. I never thought I would be without a mother whilst I was still so young. it is sometimes difficult to process and surreal, but with each day I am learning to heal and find joy in life.

In 2018, I was working as solution architect on a very large project which would see my employer start to use Oracle accounting software running on their cloud-based infrastructure instead of our existing in-house SAP software. The project was not going well as several senior architects within the company felt that the security of the system was not adequate and they required changes and assurances that were difficult to achieve. I struggled with the technical details as I did not have the necessary background, but my position in the project meant that I had responsibility for the design and implementation of the solutions. After a few weeks of this I realized that I did not want to continue to struggle with this and would like to retire.
Specific Event: Having to answer a security question in a review

Recall: I feel disgust when I watch documentaries on how our species is destroying the planet, allowing greed to cause business to not care about the health of our species and how governments lie to maintain power.  These documentaries make me not trust our society and look at people I don't know with a level of distrust until they have earned my trust.
Specific Event: How greed causes complete lack of care in humans.

Recall: I can't recall any situation that i have felt any disapproval from anyone in respects to anything, i am a very easy going guy, and tend to be approving in all areas, not wanting to offend upset people

I felt grief when my cat died We took her to the vets when she was unwell and they gave expensive medicine. A week or so later she was still severely unwell. We had to make the decision to put her down and I was in the room whilst it happened. I was devastated after and felt like i'd been emotionally hit with a hammer.

I had to pass the phone to my father dying of cancer, so he could speak to his (widowed) mother who lived 4000 miles away in Denmark to tell her he had little time left. They hadn't seen each other in person in about 4 years, that phone call was their last contact. 
Their exchange was in Danish - which I do not speak - I could roughly make out a few words, but I understood the heaviness of what was spoken.
When my father passed the phone back to me, all I could say to my grandmother in German was 'I'm sorry'. Holding back tears was hard in that moment. It was one of the hardest things in my life.

Just last week I was asked to take over a project that was struggling.  The programme leads explained the issues with me before I met with the team delivering the project.  The issues described by the project team were completely different to those explained by the programme leads.  It was if they were describing different projects.
Specific Event: The meeting with the project team.

Recall: What I once thought of as 'family'  turned their backs on me during a traumatic time, without a single word, no explanation, nothing. That was ten years ago, and it looks as though I will never know why or what happened.
Specific Event: It was sudden, and there was no explanation

Recall: It was the day of my birthday but my husband as acting like he had forgotten about it the whole day and i did not ask him but when i got home from work he surprised me with a nice gift, this bought me so much joy
Yesterday I ate a chocolate bar and felt joy. It tasted great and i was hungry. It was a bar of dark chocolate.
Left job where I was working as a temp because company was taken over and recruitment halted. Disappointed to have wasted a couple of years working for the company.
i felt disapproval when i realised that my husband was leading a double life. he was having an affair an lying to me an others, i felt anger and disapproval as he shouldnt be doig it
cat decided to wipe his bum on the floor after using litter tray, requiring extensive clear up. something that some male cats do similar to dogs
When my cousin broke the news that she was getting engaged. I was startled because she did not seem the type to ever get married, although I was very happy for her.

I had a heart operation the end of June 2021 to repair my leaking mitral valve.

It was partly a success because I suffered a stroke during the surgery which I am trying to cope with in every day life now and until the effects wear off.

However, if the mitral valve could  not be repaired by the surgeon I might have had to have it replaced with either an animal (pig) one or metal; both require Warfarin blood thinner to be taken daily for the rest of your life and the pig valve must be replaced after ten years.

I am truly Grateful that the surgeon was able to repair my own valve and I do not have to have further surgery or Warfarin daily for the rest of my life.

I felt loved when I celebrated my birthday this year and although I didn't do anything special, seeing all my friends present for me on a day that usually makes me sad made me feel good and appreciated, as if someone had finally figured out who I am

It was Saturday morning I was busy arguing with my friends who is the greatest footballer of all time my friends were voting for Cristiano and I was going for Messi. There was a final game later than the evening of a Champions League and Cristiano approved that he was the greatest of all time. That day I approved what my friends were saying.
I was working in the garden when I found a slug eating a fallen tomato. When I went to remove the tomato from the soil the slug slipped from the tomato and onto the back of my hand where it stuck.
Specific Event: It was the "idea" of the slug touching me.

Recall: I remember a time when I had been experiencing strange sensations in my abdomen, I thought the problem would resolve itself but it didn't so reluctantly and with trepidation I called the Doctor's. I was asked to go in and the Doctor said he would send me for an urgent full blood test. So for a couple of weeks I was nervous and not feeling very optimistic. I eventually received a text message telling me the result was back and non urgent. I suddenly felt more optimistic than I had done for a long while.
Specific Event: That my future wasn't as bleak as I'd imagined

Recall: When I failed my driving test in south London I was very dissapointed. I had never failed any exam in my life. I didn't have much money and had spent a lot of money on lessons. The prospect of yet more costs on further lessons was concerning.
I was thankful that the bus I was waiting on arrived on time and allowed me to get to me destination on schedule

I recently felt remorse when I told a relative that I couldn't look after there dog while they went away on holiday for 7 days. Even though I am a massive dog lover, I couldn't have the dog in my rented property and I didn't want to be left alone in there house either with just the dog for company for 7 days. I felt so guilty for saying no and it actually took me a while to pluck up the courage to actually so I couldn't do it.
Specific Event: The fact I felt I would be letting them down.

Recall: Me and my friend were talking about politics in a public park in our city. I felt disapproval when a friend of mine said that everyone, who shows signs of having a left political view is stupid.
Specific Event: My friend talking bad about specific politic group

Recall: I felt joy when I got my first kiss from a childhood girlfriend. I was playing with my friends and then she came to me, hugged me and started to kiss me. With that act, she made my day so joyful.

I was working for a school for several years and a promotion opportunity arose.  I was encouraged to apply by senior members of the team.  After weeks of preparation and work I was successful in the process and was promoted.

I went on holiday to germany and lost my passport at a festival. I was calling around the embassy and local police as well as looking for it at the ground. about 15 hours later it was fount and returned, I was extremely grateful that it was returned and it meant I wasn't stranded and able to catch my flight back.
Specific Event: the fact that it was returned

Recall: When as a young child I went to my first football game. I got to take the day off school, so I could travel there. It was a really good experience to see the ground, feel the atmosphere and see the game. It was a good game as well, so it was memorable.
Specific Event: Seeing the ground for the first time.

My son had remembered when I had told him that if you put lemons in the microwave before juicing them, it made them juicier.  So, thinking it might help the lemon, and unbeknownst to us, he decided to microwave it, but it just exploded.  He was very sad about that unfortunately, but, I'm afraid, my Mum and I laughed a lot!

I had arrived home at my dad's house in Singapore. I had just walked home from a hotel where I had been quarantined for 2 weeks since leaving the UK. It was my birthday and I was glad to be out of isolation. When I arrived home, I had received a package from my partner in the UK. It contained 5 folders worth of notes for university, my Singapore identity card, a little box with a gift necklace my partner had chosen and a thoughtfully written card. My partner went out of his way to gather these things which I was unable to get due to lockdown rules and travel restrictions. To then pack and pay for postage to ensure that the package arrived for me on my birthday... made me feel so loved and looked after.
Specific Event: Specifically, receiving the package on my birthday

Recall: I don't have a relationship with my mom - she neglected me as a child and we don't have contact these days. A few years ago, around Christmas time, she sent me a gift basket of local items from the area I now live. The gift basket, in my mind, symbolized a gift that you would give to someone you don't know very well, so they would hopefully enjoy the contents. I felt sadness about this because it was a good representation of my relationship with my mom, two people who don't know each other well, who trade safe and generic gift items. This made me sad because I felt like my mom doesn't know who I am.
Specific Event: not having a relationship with my mom
